title: Winfield-Mt. Union boys finish first at Central Lee race, girls get third
text:
Winfield-Mt. Union boys finish first at Central Lee race, girls get third Oct 15, 2015 
BY ANDY KRUTSINGER 
Mt. Pleasant News 
DONNELLSON — The Winfield-Mt. Union cross country team competed on Wednesday at Central Lee. The boys’ team came out on top, scoring 52 points and finishing just ahead of Columbus Community (59 point) for first, while the girls’ team was able to come in third, with 97 points. 
The Wolves finished the race with three runners in the top six. Gavin Benzce ran the race in 17:41 for second place. He finished just behind Josh Keller of Columbus, who ran the race in 17:39.81. Johnathon Quinn finished in fourth place, in 18:27.75, and Drake Mehaffy finished in sixth, at 19:14.69. 
Kohlton Heinzel ran in 14th place for the Wolves, in 20:00.72. Ross Vantiger was 26th, in 21:32.90. Nick Davis finished 39th, in 22:11.62, and Kane Harris was 46th, in 22:31.59. 
Cecelia Hemsworth led the girls’ team with a fifth-place time of 24:01.81. Whitney Vantiger ran 19th place, in 26:24.90. Kimberlee Warnstaff finished 21st, in 26:39.27. Isabella Mertens was 24th, in 26:53.45, and Fionna Sparrow was 28th, in 28:43.29 
W-MU will have a quick turnaround for their next meet. The Wolves will compete today (Thurs.), at Waterworks Park in Fairfield. That meet is scheduled to start at 4:30 p.m
